          <h3 class="header-medium">Comparison Area</h3>
          <div class="grid-x">
            <div class="cell medium-3 large-2 feature-image-cell">
              {{!-- TODO: Edit this placeholder image! --}}
              <img src="http://via.placeholder.com/400x400" class="feature-image">
            </div>
            <div class="cell medium-9 large-10">
              <p>The Comparison Area is the geography chosen to provide a contrast to the Selected Area. This Comparison Area is selected through the Compare to drop-down menu.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3 class="header-medium">Charts</h3>
          <div class="grid-x">
            <div class="cell medium-3 large-2 feature-image-cell">
              {{!-- TODO: Edit this placeholder image! --}}
              <img src="http://via.placeholder.com/400x400" class="feature-image">
            </div>
            <div class="cell medium-9 large-10">
              <p>Charts are provided for a selected number of topic areas on all Profile Tabs. The charts show a distribution of variables across a base universe for the Selected Area. The distribution for the Selected Area is shown in contrast to the distribution for the Comparison Area. Charts appearing in ACS tabs include Margins of Error bars. (In general, if error bars around an estimate for the Selected Area does not overlap with the error bars around an estimate for the Comparison Area, then the difference between the two estimates is statistically significant at a 90% confidence level.)</p>
            </div>
          </div>          

          <h3 class="header-medium">Drop-down List on Profile Tabs</h3>
          <div class="grid-x">
